reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars ❤️ HAD TO ORDER MORE ❤️
reviews.reviewText: I loved the first one so much, I ended up ordering more. I'm gonna buy some for gifts and my work Fleet as well. The hanging seat hooks seams very well made. Doesn't look bulky or tacky hanging on my seats. I put these in a mid size suv with Gray leather interior and mid size truck with black leather interior and it looks great in both. It's super functional and keeps items off the floor and from rolling around. Deliverywas quick and easy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These are pretty durable. The hooks are perfect for hats and purses, which is what I usually hang on them. They are a great size, the leather look matches my car. They are a little stiff but with the heat inside the car and weight of objects they get more flexible. It was easy to install onto my headrest and have held up great in the last 6 months. Definitely recommend these if you don't want cheap plastic ones of sparkling ones. I've recieved compliments on these many times!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars PLEASE READ-Be careful with these around your pets
reviews.reviewText: I love these and they are great quality but I did want to write this review to let pet owners know to be very careful. I was driving on 2 different occasions and my dogs collar got caught on the hooks. I do have a seat belt for my dog in the car but he was not buckled in so obviously that is on me but the risks of these never crossed my mind when I put them in my car. I just wanted to put this out there just to make others aware so we can all keep our fur babies safe.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are nice, really nice.
reviews.reviewText: I am impressed. I really wanted hooks in the car for holding grocery and other bags, but husband-who loves new car-has been, um, choosey? So we haven't kept any yet and really I'm glad he was because these are soooooo much better. Yes, you do have to loop bags carefully as the hook doesn't just stick out, but-the hook doesn't stick out, ya know? We aren't catching things on it when we don't mean to. They are real metal-not plastic-got caught on that once-and if they aren't real leather they are the best faux I've ever seen and at 50 y/o how many purses and boots/shoes have I seen, right? We are so impressed. We got cream for behind the front seats as our leather is cream and black for behind the rear seats because the car carpet runs up the back and it's black. Both look equally good. Very happy with purchase.

reviews.reviewText: These hooks are durable and strong. I have one on my front passenger seat.
